SIMPLE: ethylidene
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ethylidene
<hw>E*thyl"i*dene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An
unsymmetrical, divalent, hydrocarbon radical, <chform>C2H4</chform>
metameric with ethylene but written thus, <chform>CH3.CH=</chform> to
distinguish it from the symmetrical ethylene, <chform>CH2=CH2</chform>.
Its compounds are derived from aldehyde. Formerly called also
<altname>ethidene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ethylin</ent>⟦br⟧
